text: Little things that I noticed: Mavis is wearing a wedding ring so it's been at least a couple years since the last movie. The werewolf puppies are teenagers now (awe!). The trailer spans a couple years cuz in the beginning its Dennis' 1st birthday and later on it's his 4th birthday. It probably does a little montage at the beginning of Mavis having Dennis and then the first couple years, and the rest of the movie is when he's 4.  Also, Johnny looks a little different (i.e. older) but not by much and Mavis looks the same which isn't surprising cuz vampire's age very slowly. Which brings me to my #1 question: How are they gonna make their marriage work if he ages so much faster than her? I've discussed this with my friend and we came to two possibilities: They're going to change him at some point or they already have. As for the whole Dennis being half and half, I'm not sure if they're really going 'Twilight lore' on us but if so then he'll age like a human but live as long as vampires do. I wonder if they're gonna touch base on all the concerns they had, if any, about Dennis. The way Wayne was so knowledgeable about how he has until he turns 5 to get his fangs, I'm gonna say that it's not all that rare at this point. Which means they've all interacted with humans other than Johnny at this point. One other thing I'm wondering is if Drac's mom is still alive along with his dad. Or Martha's parents. That'd be sweet to meet them. I'm glad we get to know Johnny's parents and that they know the truth about Mavis' family. ANYWAY, I looked way too into this, but there you go.
